("7275","505","intro_video_video","<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EpKDPXXBcJo\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>"),
("7276","505","_intro_video_video","field_61983b7478b26"),
("7277","505","intro_video_title","Blockchain explained"),
("7278","505","_intro_video_title","field_61983b7d78b27"),
("7279","505","intro_video_excerpt","Blockchains are public ledgers where all transactions and changes are grouped in blocks. Together these blocks form a chain, representing the complete history of the ledger. This is where we get the term blockchain from.\r\n\r\nThis short video explains what a blockchain is and what different innovations we can expect utilising this technological breakthrough."),
("7280","505","_intro_video_excerpt","field_61983b8178b28"),
("7281","505","intro_video",""),
("7282","505","_intro_video","field_61983b6a78b25"),
("7283","505","intro_items2","4"),
("7284","505","_intro_items2","field_61983b9378b29"),
("7285","505","intro_items_0_title","cryptocurrencies?"),
("7286","505","_intro_items_0_title","field_61983b1578b22"),
("7287","505","intro_items_0_excerpt","Cryptocurrencies are cryptographic tokens that exist on distributed computer networks. They allow anyone to freely exchange value and information without the need for third parties, facilitating peer to peer exchange without any central points of failure or control. The underlying technology that has made this possible is known as blockchain or distributed ledger technology."),
("7288","505","_intro_items_0_excerpt","field_61983b1c78b23"),
("7289","505","intro_items_1_title","BLOCKCHAIN"),
("7290","505","_intro_items_1_title","field_61983b1578b22"),
("7291","505","intro_items_1_excerpt","Blockchains are distributed computer networks, consisting of participants that verify, maintain and secure all transactions and changes made within the network. Information saved on a blockchain cannot be changed, creating an immutable history. That is why blockchains are ideal for the digital representation of value, without the problem of double spending."),
("7292","505","_intro_items_1_excerpt","field_61983b1c78b23"),
("7293","505","intro_items2_0_title","Secure and trustworthy"),
("7294","505","_intro_items2_0_title","field_61983b9378b2a"),
("7295","505","intro_items2_0_excerpt","Due to their decentralized nature, cryptocurrencies cannot be manipulated by any one party"),
("7296","505","_intro_items2_0_excerpt","field_61983b9378b2b"),
("7297","505","intro_items2_1_title","Store of value"),
("7298","505","_intro_items2_1_title","field_61983b9378b2a"),
("7299","505","intro_items2_1_excerpt","Because of their guaranteed and predictable supply, cryptocurrencies are well suited as a store of value."),
("7300","505","_intro_items2_1_excerpt","field_61983b9378b2b"),
("7301","505","intro_items2_2_title","Fast and borderless"),
("7302","505","_intro_items2_2_title","field_61983b9378b2a"),
("7303","505","intro_items2_2_excerpt","Payment with cryptocurrency is faster and much less expensive than traditional payment solutions."),
("7304","505","_intro_items2_2_excerpt","field_61983b9378b2b"),
("7305","505","intro_items2_3_title","Total control and ownership"),
("7306","505","_intro_items2_3_title","field_61983b9378b2a"),
("7307","505","intro_items2_3_excerpt","Control of cryptocurrencies lies completely with the owner, totally independent from any authority."),
("7308","505","_intro_items2_3_excerpt","field_61983b9378b2b"),
